\section{Formatting progress summaries}

The list output needs the same status wording whether we render a Rich
table for a terminal or tab-separated rows for a script.

<<functions>>=
def format_progress_status(progress: ProgressState) -> str:
    """Return a short status label for list output."""

    status = (
        "completed"
        if progress.finished
        else f"{progress.completed_steps}/{progress.total_steps} complete"
    )
    return status
@


Let's verify that unfinished tutorials show both counts.

<<test functions>>=
