\section{Formatting step prompts}

Each step opens a fresh interaction, so the CLI must print the
instructions before that interaction starts.  We author that
student-facing text as Markdown and render it with Rich [[Markdown]] so
paragraphs and inline commands read cleanly in an ordinary terminal.

A little vertical space around the body matters too.  Without it, the
workspace line, the instructions, and the interaction reminder blur
together into one dense block of text.

The reminder itself depends on the step mode.  Shell steps ask the
student to exit the shell, while editor steps ask them to save and quit
the editor.

<<functions>>=
def render_step_prompt(
    console: Console,
    tutorial_title: str,
    step_number: int,
    total_steps: int,
    step_title: str,
    instructions: str,
    workspace: str,
    *,
    edit_file: str | None = None,
) -> None:
    """Render the prompt shown before one interactive step."""

    console.print()
    console.print(tutorial_title, style="bold")
    console.print(
        f"Step {step_number}/{total_steps}: {step_title}",
        style="bold",
    )
    console.print(f"Workspace: {workspace}", style="dim")
    if edit_file is not None:
        console.print(f"File: {edit_file}", style="dim")
    console.print()
    console.print(Markdown(instructions))
    console.print()
    if edit_file is None:
        console.print(
            "Exit the shell when you want the tutorial to validate the step.",
            style="dim",
        )
    else:
        console.print(
            "Save the file and quit the editor when you want the tutorial "
            "to validate the step.",
            style="dim",
        )
    console.print()
@

